  <mainDescription>&lt;a id=&quot;Top&quot; name=&quot;Top&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;XE_tool_specialist_(role)__description_of&quot;&#xD;
name=&quot;XE_tool_specialist_(role)__description_of&quot;>&lt;/a>&lt;a id=&quot;Description&quot; name=&quot;Description&quot;>&lt;/a></mainDescription>
  <skills>&lt;a id=&quot;Skills&quot; name=&quot;Skills&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p align=&quot;left&quot;>&#xD;
    An individual playing the role of a &lt;a class=&quot;PresentationName&quot; guid=&quot;{67BD4971-9474-470E-945B-6F8A380FA8FC}&quot;>Tool&#xD;
    Specialist&lt;/a> needs to have a broad set of skills. This includes an understanding of the underlying processes used by&#xD;
    the project, and for this training might be required prior to project startup. General systematic analysis skills are&#xD;
    beneficial when comparing and selecting tools for the project. Knowledge of the development platform(s) is required, on&#xD;
    networking issues in particular. A person acting as a &lt;a class=&quot;PresentationName&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;{67BD4971-9474-470E-945B-6F8A380FA8FC}&quot;>Tool Specialist&lt;/a> also needs good communication skills and a&#xD;
    'service-minded' attitude, since she or he is likely to be a support contact point for the project members, on&#xD;
    installation and other tool troubleshooting issues.&#xD;
&lt;/p></skills>
  <assignmentApproaches>&lt;a id=&quot;RoleAssignment&quot; name=&quot;RoleAssignment&quot;>&lt;/a> &#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The &lt;a class=&quot;PresentationName&quot; guid=&quot;{67BD4971-9474-470E-945B-6F8A380FA8FC}&quot;>Tool Specialist&lt;/a> role can be assigned&#xD;
    in the following ways:&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;ul>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Assign one or more staff members to perform both the &lt;a class=&quot;PresentationName&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{67BD4971-9474-470E-945B-6F8A380FA8FC}&quot;>Tool Specialist&lt;/a> and Implementer roles. This is a commonly adopted&#xD;
        approach, especially in small-to-mid-sized teams, and capitalizes on the common development skills that Implementer&#xD;
        role shares with this role.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
    &lt;li>&#xD;
        Assign one staff member to perform the &lt;a class=&quot;PresentationName&quot;&#xD;
        guid=&quot;{67BD4971-9474-470E-945B-6F8A380FA8FC}&quot;>Tool Specialist&lt;/a> role only. This is a commonly adopted approach&#xD;
        and is particularly suitable for large teams or smaller teams where effective tool support and process automation&#xD;
        is a key aspect of the projects development plan.&#xD;
    &lt;/li>&#xD;
&lt;/ul></assignmentApproaches>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:RoleDescription>
